{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f5c7aefd-456e-4910-8253-159e83d5f6e4","content":"Analyzing .NET crash dumps is outside the scope of the tools I have here (the dump-collect skill only covers **capturing** dumps, not analyzing them). However, here's how you can investigate:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (`printexception`) | Print last exception details |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM issues) |\n| `dso` (`dumpstackobjects`) | Objects on the stack |\n\n**Using Visual Studio** (Windows):\n- Open the `.dmp` file directly → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**\n\n**Using `lldb`** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load /path/to/libsosplugin.so\nclrstack\npe\n```\n\nWould you like help setting up any of these tools, or do you have a specific error/symptom you'd like guidance on?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a6acb4bd-6dac-4977-a0ba-0bb621da68eb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze, not collect.\n\nI should help them directly with guidance on analyzing crash dumps.","outputTokens":442},"id":"2e798f73-06d6-481e-94b3-2484b866b70c","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:09:38.816Z","parentId":"4b545cf3-0952-4815-99a3-5b762b6b748b"}
